{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI"]]},"sections":[],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"attribute","text":"@frozen"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"ProposedViewSize"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Overview","anchor":"overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"During layout in OpenSwiftUI, views choose their own size, but they do that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"in response to a size proposal from their parent view. When you create"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"a custom layout using the "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Layout","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" protocol, your layout container"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"participates in this process using "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ProposedViewSize"},{"type":"text","text":" instances."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The layout protocol’s methods take a proposed size input that you"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"can take into account when arranging views and calculating the size of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the composite container. Similarly, your layout proposes a size to each"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of its own subviews when it measures and places them."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Layout containers typically measure their subviews by proposing several"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"sizes and looking at the responses. The container can use this information"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to decide how to allocate space among its subviews. 